#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Shackles "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Piyasutta "
msgstr "4. Loved "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.72, pts2ed1.165, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.4:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.3"
msgid "“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "“Just now, sir, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.4"
msgid "‘kesaṃ nu kho piyo attā, kesaṃ appiyo attā’ti? "
msgstr "‘Who are those who love themselves? And who are those who don’t love themselves?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.4:1.5"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.6"
msgid "‘ye ca kho keci kāyena duccaritaṃ caranti, vācāya duccaritaṃ caranti, manasā duccaritaṃ caranti; "
msgstr "‘Those who do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.7"
msgid "tesaṃ appiyo attā. "
msgstr "don’t love themselves. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.8"
msgid "Kiñcāpi te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "Even though they may say: "

# NOTE: close quote incorrect in MS.
msgctxt "sn3.4:1.9"
msgid "“piyo no attā”ti, atha kho tesaṃ appiyo attā’. "
msgstr "“I love myself”, they don’t really. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.11"
msgid "Yañhi appiyo appiyassa kareyya, taṃ te attanāva attano karonti; "
msgstr "It’s because they treat themselves like an enemy. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.12"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ appiyo attā. "
msgstr "That’s why they don’t love themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.4:1.13"
msgid "Ye ca kho keci kāyena sucaritaṃ caranti, vācāya sucaritaṃ caranti, manasā sucaritaṃ caranti; "
msgstr "Those who do good things by way of body, speech, and mind "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.14"
msgid "tesaṃ piyo attā. "
msgstr "do love themselves. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.15"
msgid "Kiñcāpi te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "Even though they may say: "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.16"
msgid "‘appiyo no attā’ti; atha kho tesaṃ piyo attā. "
msgstr "“I don’t love myself”, they do really. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.17"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.18"
msgid "Yañhi piyo piyassa kareyya, taṃ te attanāva attano karonti; "
msgstr "It’s because they treat themselves like a loved one. "

msgctxt "sn3.4:1.19"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ piyo attā”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why they do love themselves.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn3.4:2.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, mahārāja, evametaṃ, mahārāja. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, great king! That’s so true!” said the Buddha. And he repeated the king’s statement, adding: "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.2"
msgid "Ye hi keci, mahārāja, kāyena duccaritaṃ caranti, vācāya duccaritaṃ caranti, manasā duccaritaṃ caranti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.3"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ appiyo attā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.4"
msgid "Kiñcāpi te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.5"
msgid "‘piyo no attā’ti, atha kho tesaṃ appiyo attā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.7"
msgid "Yañhi, mahārāja, appiyo appiyassa kareyya, taṃ te attanāva attano karonti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.8"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ appiyo attā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.9"
msgid "Ye ca kho keci, mahārāja, kāyena sucaritaṃ caranti, vācāya sucaritaṃ caranti, manasā sucaritaṃ caranti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.10"
msgid "tesaṃ piyo attā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.11"
msgid "Kiñcāpi te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.12"
msgid "‘appiyo no attā’ti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.13"
msgid "atha kho tesaṃ piyo attā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.14"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.15"
msgid "Yañhi, mahārāja, piyo piyassa kareyya, taṃ te attanāva attano karonti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.4:2.16"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ piyo attā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.4:2.17"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn3.4:3.1"
msgid "“Attānañce piyaṃ jaññā, "
msgstr "“If you regard yourself as loved, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:3.2"
msgid "na naṃ pāpena saṃyuje; "
msgstr "you wouldn’t yoke yourself to wickedness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:3.3"
msgid "Na hi taṃ sulabhaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "For happiness is not easy to find "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:3.4"
msgid "sukhaṃ dukkaṭakārinā. "
msgstr "by someone who does bad deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.166, sc4
msgctxt "sn3.4:4.1"
msgid "Antakenādhipannassa, "
msgstr "When you’re seized by the terminator "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:4.2"
msgid "jahato mānusaṃ bhavaṃ; "
msgstr "as you give up your human life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:4.3"
msgid "Kiñhi tassa sakaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "what can you call your own? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:4.4"
msgid "kiñca ādāya gacchati; "
msgstr "What do you take when you go? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:4.5"
msgid "Kiñcassa anugaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "What goes with you, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: anapāyinī → anupāyinī (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.4:4.6"
msgid "chāyāva anapāyinī. "
msgstr "like a shadow that never leaves? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.4:5.1"
msgid "Ubho puññañca pāpañca, "
msgstr "Both the good and the bad "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:5.2"
msgid "yaṃ macco kurute idha; "
msgstr "that a mortal does in this life "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:5.3"
msgid "Tañhi tassa sakaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "is what they can call their own. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: taṃva → tañca (sabbattha)
msgctxt "sn3.4:5.4"
msgid "taṃva ādāya gacchati; "
msgstr "That’s what they take when they go. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Taṃvassa → tañcassa (bj, s1-3, km, pts2) | taṃ cassa (pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.4:5.5"
msgid "Taṃvassa anugaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "That’s what goes with them, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:5.6"
msgid "chāyāva anapāyinī. "
msgstr "like a shadow that never leaves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn3.4:6.1"
msgid "Tasmā kareyya kalyāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "That’s why you should do good, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:6.2"
msgid "nicayaṃ samparāyikaṃ; "
msgstr "investing in the future life. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:6.3"
msgid "Puññāni paralokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "The good deeds of sentient beings "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.4:6.4"
msgid "patiṭṭhā honti pāṇinan”ti. "
msgstr "support them in the next world.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
